      • withTimeSource

        public EventTime.Builder<_B> withTimeSource(Device timeSource)
        This is an optional element to be used to indicate the time source that the event creation time has been synchronised with. In most circumstances it is assumed that the event time has been synchronised with the corporate time service where the generating device resides so the inclusion of this element is not required.

        Sets the new value of "timeSource" (any previous value will be replaced)

        Parameters:
        timeSource - New value of the "timeSource" property.

      • withTimeSource

        public Device.Builder<? extends EventTime.Builder<_B>> withTimeSource()
        This is an optional element to be used to indicate the time source that the event creation time has been synchronised with. In most circumstances it is assumed that the event time has been synchronised with the corporate time service where the generating device resides so the inclusion of this element is not required.

        Returns the existing builder or a new builder to build the value of the "timeSource" property. Use Device.Builder.end() to return to the current builder.

        Returns:
        A new builder to build the value of the "timeSource" property. Use Device.Builder.end() to return to the current builder.
